The objective of this course is to teach some classic deterministic optimization and modern large-scale stochastic optimization algorithms for solving ML/AI problems. Upon completion of the course, students will:
1. be able to name classical stochastic optimization algorithms and analyze their convergence properties;
2. be able to evaluate and compare the performance of different optimization algorithms for solving the same problem;
3. be able to apply tuning strategies to improve the performance of an optimization algorithm;
4. be able to design some new optimization algorithms for solving large-scale ML problems.
